==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preponderant
<hw>Pre*pon"der*ant</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praeponderans</ets>, <ets>-antis</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧pond⟦eacute⟧rant</ets>. See <er>Preponderate</er>.]</ety>
<def>Preponderating; outweighing; overbalancing; -- used literally and
figuratively; <as>as, a <ex>preponderant</ex> weight; of
<ex>preponderant</ex> importance.</as></def> --
<wordforms><wf>Pre*pon"der*ant*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preponderate</ent>⟦br⟧
